    <fr:title text="Algebraic Theory of Global Mutable Finite State">Algebraic Theory of Global Mutable Finite State</fr:title>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>The <fr:link href="/L94N/" title="Finitary Algebraic Theory" uri="https://um-catlab.github.io/L94N/" display-uri="L94N" type="local">algebraic theory</fr:link> of global mutable finite state for a finite set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> has operations</html:p>
    <html:p>
      <html:ol><html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[l(S)]]></fr:tex>, short for "lookup"</html:li> <html:li>For each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s : S]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u{[s]}(1)]]></fr:tex> short for "update"</html:li></html:ol>
    </html:p>
    <html:p>subject to the equations</html:p>
    <html:p>
      <html:ol><html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[l(\lambda  s. u{[s]}(x)) = x]]></fr:tex></html:li> <html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u{[s]}(u{[s']}(x)) = u{[s']}(x)]]></fr:tex></html:li> <html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[u{[s]}(l(t)) = u{[s]}(t(s))]]></fr:tex></html:li></html:ol>
    </html:p>
    <html:p>Intuitively the lookup operation branches on the value of the state, picking the appopriate argument as continuation and update sets the value of the state and then proceeds with the continuation.</html:p>
    <html:p>The equations say that (1) updating the state to what you just read does nothing (2) updating overwrites a preceding update and (3) lookup executes the continuation corresponding to the most recent update.</html:p>
    <html:p>The <fr:link href="/L94N/" title="Finitary Algebraic Theory" uri="https://um-catlab.github.io/L94N/" display-uri="L94N" type="local">free state algebra</fr:link> on a set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> can be constructed explicitly as the stateful functions <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(S \times  X)^S]]></fr:tex> and the state monad is the corresponding free algebra monad.</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
